",\"Glob\",\"Grep\",\"Edit\",\"Write\",\"Bash\",\"Agent\",\"TodoWrite\"],\"query\":\"select:Read,Glob,Grep,Edit,Write,Bash,Agent,TodoWrite\",\"total_deferred_tools\":18}}\n{\"type\":\"rate_limit_event\",\"rate_limit_info\":{\"status\":\"allowed\",\"resetsAt\":1772848800,\"rateLimitType\":\"five_hour\",\"overageStatus\":\"rejected\",\"overageDisabledReason\":\"org_level_disabled\",\"isUsingOverage\":false},\"uuid\":\"e1a3720c-35bc-4f55-b788-42de33f7b9b3\",\"session_id\":\"686830cd-8617-4d34-827b-86a53226e411\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01SViLYfysTt2EVhiPvSRSc2\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"\\n\\nLet me start by reading the design doc and current source files to understand what's needed.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10098,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":7586,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":10098},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"686830cd-8617-4d34-827b-86a53226e411\",\"uuid\":\"6daa949a-c848-473d-94a4-eca0eb6009a8\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01SViLYfysTt2EVhiPvSRSc2\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_011Z54jhzgxE2xeQVdemVMRj\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10098,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":7586,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":10098},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"686830cd-8617-4d34-827b-86a53226e411\",\"uuid\":\"d711d322-cf4b-4041-900b-cb7471af490d\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_011Z54jhzgxE2xeQVdemVMRj\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Project Pages Design\\n     2→\\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\\n     4→**Status:** Design\\n     5→\\n     6→## Problem\\n     7→\\n     8→The projects landing page shows only health dots and a \\\"View Runs\\\" link. There is no\\n     9→dedicated project page. Useful project-level information and controls are either missing\\n    10→or buried in other views.\\n    11→\\n    12→## Goal\\n    13→\\n    14→Add a dedicated `/projects/{name}` page with three panels:\\n    15→\\n    16→1. **Orchestrator control** — view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\\n    17→2. **Project info** — Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\\n    18→3. **Workflow view** — read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\\n    19→\\n    20→## Route\\n    21→\\n    22→```\\n    23→GET /projects/{name}\\n    24→```\\n    25→\\n    26→`{name}` is the project label (same string used in `/api/projects/{name}/trigger`).\\n    27→The handler resolves the label back to a project directory via `projectLabels()`.\\n    28→\\n    29→Project cards on the landing page link to `/projects/{name}` instead of\\n    30→`/runs?project=X`. The project page includes a compact recent-runs strip (last 10 dots)\\n    31→and a \\\"View all runs\\\" link to the filtered runs list.\\n    32→\\n    33→## Panel 1: Orchestrator Control\\n    34→\\n    35→### Display\\n    36→- Status line: `Enabled / Disabled`, in-flight run count, concurrency limit\\n    37→- Toggle button: **Enable** / **Disable** (controls the auto-poll loop for this project)\\n    38→- Concurrency override: number input + **Apply** button (runtime only, resets on daemon restart)\\n    39→\\n    40→### API additions\\n    41→\\n    42→```\\n    43→GET  /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\\n    44→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start\\n    45→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop\\n    46→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency   body: {\\\"concurrency\\\": N}\\n    47→```\\n    48→\\n    49→`GET` response:\\n    50→```json\\n    51→{\\n    52→  \\\"enabled\\\": true,\\n    53→  \\\"in_flight\\\": 1,\\n    54→  \\\"concurrency\\\": 2\\n    55→}\\n    56→```\\n    57→\\n    58→The orchestrator currently has no per-project enable/disable concept. We add an\\n    59→`enabled` flag to `ProjectConfig` (default true when registered). Start/stop toggle\\n    60→this flag. When disabled, `Run()` returns 0 without dispatching.\\n    61→\\n    62→Concurrency override updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in memory only.\\n    63→\\n    64→The Handler needs a reference to the `*orchestrator.Orchestrator` (or a minimal\\n    65→interface exposing `Status(dir)`, `SetEnabled(dir, bool)`, `SetConcurrency(dir, int)`,\\n    66→`InFlight(dir)`). Wire this in via a `HandlerOption`.\\n    67→\\n    68→## Panel 2: Project Info\\n    69→\\n    70→### Display\\n    71→- **Docker image**: read the `FROM` line(s) from `.cloche/Dockerfile`. Show the last\\n    72→  non-builder stage's base image (i.e. the stage that produces the final image).\\n    73→- **Project version**: integer, sourced from `.cloche/version` (see Project Versioning\\n    74→  design). Display as `v3`.\\n    75→- **Prompt file history**: for each file under `.cloche/prompts/`, show a timeline of\\n    76→  changes:\\n    77→  - List of git commits that touched the file (short SHA, date, message)\\n    78→  - Click a commit entry to expand and show a unified diff inline\\n    79→\\n    80→### API additions\\n    81→\\n    82→```\\n    83→GET /api/projects/{name}/info\\n    84→```\\n    85→\\n    86→Response:\\n    87→```json\\n    88→{\\n    89→  \\\"docker_image\\\": \\\"ubuntu:24.04\\\",\\n    90→  \\\"version\\\": 3,\\n    91→  \\\"prompt_files\\\": [\\n    92→    {\\n    93→      \\\"path\\\": \\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\",\\n    94→      \\\"history\\\": [\\n    95→        {\\\"sha\\\": \\\"abc1234\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-05\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"evolution: tighten scope\\\"},\\n    96→        {\\\"sha\\\": \\\"def5678\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-01\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"init\\\"}\\n    97→      ]\\n    98→    }\\n    99→  ]\\n   100→}\\n   101→```\\n   102→\\n   103→Implementation: run `git log --follow --oneline -- <file>` in the project directory\\n   104→via `exec.Command`. Diff for a specific commit loaded lazily on click via:\\n   105→\\n   106→```\\n   107→GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=.cloche/prompts/implement.md&sha=abc1234\\n   108→```\\n   109→\\n   110→Returns plain text unified diff (`git show <sha> -- <file>`).\\n   111→\\n   112→## Panel 3: Workflow View\\n   113→\\n   114→### Display\\n   115→- Tabs if multiple `*.cloche` files exist in `.cloche/` (excluding `host.cloche`)\\n   116→- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\\n   117→  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent / script)\\n   118→  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\\n   119→  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\\n   120→- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\\n   121→  - Step name and type\\n   122→  - Results list\\n   123→  - `max_attempts` if set\\n   124→  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\\n   125→  - For script steps: the command string or contents of the referenced script file\\n   126→  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\\n   127→\\n   128→### DAG rendering\\n   129→Use a simple client-side layout: no heavy library. Steps are laid out left-to-right in\\n   130→topological order. SVG arrows connect boxes. For the initial implementation, a linear\\n   131→column layout (one step per row) is acceptable if the graph is a DAG with no parallel\\n   132→branches; upgrade to a proper layered layout when parallel branches are added.\\n   133→\\n   134→### API additions\\n   135→\\n   136→```\\n   137→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\\n   138→```\\n   139→\\n   140→Response:\\n   141→```json\\n   142→[\\n   143→  {\\n   144→    \\\"name\\\": \\\"develop\\\",\\n   145→    \\\"file\\\": \\\".cloche/develop.cloche\\\",\\n   146→    \\\"steps\\\": [\\n   147→      {\\n   148→        \\\"name\\\": \\\"implement\\\",\\n   149→        \\\"type\\\": \\\"agent\\\",\\n   150→        \\\"results\\\": [\\\"success\\\", \\\"fail\\\"],\\n   151→        \\\"config\\\": {\\\"prompt\\\": \\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\", \\\"max_attempts\\\": null}\\n   152→      },\\n   153→      ...\\n   154→    ],\\n   155→    \\\"wires\\\": [\\n   156→      {\\\"from\\\": \\\"implement\\\", \\\"result\\\": \\\"success\\\", \\\"to\\\": \\\"test\\\"},\\n   157→      ...\\n   158→    ],\\n   159→    \\\"entry_step\\\": \\\"implement\\\"\\n   160→  }\\n   161→]\\n   162→```\\n   163→\\n   164→```\\n   165→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\\n   166→```\\n   167→\\n   168→Returns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text).\\n   169→If the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly.\\n   170→\\n   171→## Template / file changes\\n   172→\\n   173→- New template: `templates/project_detail.html`\\n   174→- New page registered in `NewHandler`: `\\\"project_detail\\\"`\\n   175→- New routes registered in `NewHandler` mux\\n   176→- Handler struct gains an optional orchestrator interface field (via `HandlerOption`)\\n   177→\\n   178→## Not in scope\\n   179→\\n   180→- Editing workflow files from the UI\\n   181→- Evolution history of workflow structure (just current state)\\n   182→- Persisting concurrency overrides to disk\\n   183→\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"686830cd-8617-4d34-827b-86a53226e411\",\"uuid\":\"d5ac125e-6822-4d43-b6e8-26b7506cba6c\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md\",\"content\":\"# Project Pages Design\\n\\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\\n**Status:** Design\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nThe projects landing page shows only health dots and a \\\"View Runs\\\" link. There is no\\ndedicated project page. Useful project-level information and controls are either missing\\nor buried in other views.\\n\\n## Goal\\n\\nAdd a dedicated `/projects/{name}` page with three panels:\\n\\n1. **Orchestrator control** — view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\\n2. **Project info** — Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\\n3. **Workflow view** — read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\\n\\n## Route\\n\\n```\\nGET /projects/{name}\\n```\\n\\n`{name}` is the project label (same string used in `/api/projects/{name}/trigger`).\\nThe handler resolves the label back to a project directory via `projectLabels()`.\\n\\nProject cards on the landing page link to `/projects/{name}` instead of\\n`/runs?project=X`. The project page includes a compact recent-runs strip (last 10 dots)\\nand a \\\"View all runs\\\" link to the filtered runs list.\\n\\n## Panel 1: Orchestrator Control\\n\\n### Display\\n- Status line: `Enabled / Disabled`, in-flight run count, concurrency limit\\n- Toggle button: **Enable** / **Disable** (controls the auto-poll loop for this project)\\n- Concurrency override: number input + **Apply** button (runtime only, resets on daemon restart)\\n\\n### API additions\\n\\n```\\nGET  /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start\\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop\\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency   body: {\\\"concurrency\\\": N}\\n```\\n\\n`GET` response:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"enabled\\\": true,\\n  \\\"in_flight\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"concurrency\\\": 2\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe orchestrator currently has no per-project enable/disable concept. We add an\\n`enabled` flag to `ProjectConfig` (default true when registered). Start/stop toggle\\nthis flag. When disabled, `Run()` returns 0 without dispatching.\\n\\nConcurrency override updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in memory only.\\n\\nThe Handler needs a reference to the `*orchestrator.Orchestrator` (or a minimal\\ninterface exposing `Status(dir)`, `SetEnabled(dir, bool)`, `SetConcurrency(dir, int)`,\\n`InFlight(dir)`). Wire this in via a `HandlerOption`.\\n\\n## Panel 2: Project Info\\n\\n### Display\\n- **Docker image**: read the `FROM` line(s) from `.cloche/Dockerfile`. Show the last\\n  non-builder stage's base image (i.e. the stage that produces the final image).\\n- **Project version**: integer, sourced from `.cloche/version` (see Project Versioning\\n  design). Display as `v3`.\\n- **Prompt file history**: for each file under `.cloche/prompts/`, show a timeline of\\n  changes:\\n  - List of git commits that touched the file (short SHA, date, message)\\n  - Click a commit entry to expand and show a unified diff inline\\n\\n### API additions\\n\\n```\\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info\\n```\\n\\nResponse:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"docker_image\\\": \\\"ubuntu:24.04\\\",\\n  \\\"version\\\": 3,\\n  \\\"prompt_files\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\",\\n      \\\"history\\\": [\\n        {\\\"sha\\\": \\\"abc1234\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-05\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"evolution: tighten scope\\\"},\\n        {\\\"sha\\\": \\\"def5678\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-01\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"init\\\"}\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\nImplementation: run `git log --follow --oneline -- <file>` in the project directory\\nvia `exec.Command`. Diff for a specific commit loaded lazily on click via:\\n\\n```\\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=.cloche/prompts/implement.md&sha=abc1234\\n```\\n\\nReturns plain text unified diff (`git show <sha> -- <file>`).\\n\\n## Panel 3: Workflow View\\n\\n### Display\\n- Tabs if multiple `*.cloche` files exist in `.cloche/` (excluding `host.cloche`)\\n- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\\n  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent / script)\\n  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\\n  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\\n- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\\n  - Step name and type\\n  - Results list\\n  - `max_attempts` if set\\n  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\\n  - For script steps: the command string or contents of the referenced script file\\n  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\\n\\n### DAG rendering\\nUse a simple client-side layout: no heavy library. Steps are laid out left-to-right in\\ntopological order. SVG arrows connect boxes. For the initial implementation, a linear\\ncolumn layout (one step per row) is acceptable if the graph is a DAG with no parallel\\nbranches; upgrade to a proper layered layout when parallel branches are added.\\n\\n### API additions\\n\\n```\\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\\n```\\n\\nResponse:\\n```json\\n[\\n  {\\n    \\\"name\\\": \\\"develop\\\",\\n    \\\"file\\\": \\\".cloche/develop.cloche\\\",\\n    \\\"steps\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"implement\\\",\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"agent\\\",\\n        \\\"results\\\": [\\\"success\\\", \\\"fail\\\"],\\n        \\\"config\\\": {\\\"prompt\\\": \\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\", \\\"max_attempts\\\": null}\\n      },\\n      ...\\n    ],\\n    \\\"wires\\\": [\\n      {\\\"from\\\": \\\"implement\\\", \\\"result\\\": \\\"success\\\", \\\"to\\\": \\\"test\\\"},\\n      ...\\n    ],\\n    \\\"entry_step\\\": \\\"implement\\\"\\n  }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n```\\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\\n```\\n\\nReturns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text).\\nIf the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly.\\n\\n## Template / file changes\\n\\n- New template: `templates/project_detail.html`\\n- New page registered in `NewHandler`: `\\\"project_detail\\\"`\\n- New routes registered in `NewHandler` mux\\n- Handler struct gains an optional orchestrator interface field (via `HandlerOption`)\\n\\n## Not in scope\\n\\n- Editing workflow files from the UI\\n- Evolution history of workflow structure (just current state)\\n- Persisting concurrency overrides to disk\\n\",\"numLines\":183,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":183}}}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01SViLYfysTt2EVhiPvSRSc2\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01GHutPCZg5BLC7dcuRu2A97\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/workspace/internal/orchestrator/orchestrator.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10098,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":7586,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":10098},\"output_tokens\":2,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"686830cd-8617-4d34-827b-86a53226e411\",\"uuid\":\"6df11c57-d126-4492-9a69-77a07d97cc07\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01GHutPCZg5BLC7dcuRu2A97\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→package orchestrator\\n     2→\\n     3→import (\\n     4→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n     5→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n     6→\\t\\\"log\\\"\\n     7→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n     8→\\t\\\"path/filepath\\\"\\n     9→\\t\\\"sync\\\"\\n    10→\\n    11→\\t\\\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/config\\\"\\n    12→\\t\\\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\\\"\\n    13→\\t\\\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\\\"\\n    14→)\\n    15→\\n    16→// RunDispatcher dispatches a workflow run and returns the run ID.\\n    17→type RunDispatcher func(ctx context.Context, workflowName, projectDir, prompt string) (string, error)\\n    18→\\n    19→// ProjectConfig holds orchestration settings for a single project.\\n    20→type ProjectConfig struct {\\n    21→\\tDir         string\\n    22→\\tWorkflow    string\\n    23→\\tConcurrency int\\n    24→\\tTracker     ports.TaskTracker\\n    25→\\tEnabled     bool\\n    26→}\\n    27→\\n    28→// ParseHostWorkflowFunc parses a host.cloche file and returns the named workflow.\\n    29→type ParseHostWorkflowFunc func(input string) (*domain.Workflow, error)\\n    30→\\n    31→// Orchestrator pulls ready tasks and dispatches workflow runs, respecting\\n    32→// per-project concurrency limits.\\n    33→type Orchestrator struct {\\n    34→\\tpromptGen          PromptGenerator\\n    35→\\tdispatch           RunDispatcher\\n    36→\\tmu                 sync.Mutex\\n    37→\\tprojects           map[string]*ProjectConfig // keyed by Dir\\n    38→\\tinFlight           map[string]int            // keyed by Dir\\n    39→\\tinFlightTasks      map[string]string         // runID -> taskID\\n    40→\\tinFlightTaskSet    map[string]map[string]bool // projectDir -> set of taskIDs in flight\\n    41→\\thostRunner         *HostRunner\\n    42→\\tparseHostWorkflow  ParseHostWorkflowFunc\\n    43→}\\n    44→\\n    45→// New creates an Orchestrator.\\n    46→func New(promptGen PromptGenerator, dispatch RunDispatcher, opts ...OrchestratorOption) *Orchestrator {\\n    47→\\to := &Orchestrator{\\n    48→\\t\\tpromptGen:       promptGen,\\n    49→\\t\\tdispatch:        dispatch,\\n    50→\\t\\tprojects:        make(map[string]*ProjectConfig),\\n    51→\\t\\tinFlight:        make(map[string]int),\\n    52→\\t\\tinFlightTasks:   make(map[string]string),\\n    53→\\t\\tinFlightTaskSet: make(map[string]map[string]bool),\\n    54→\\t}\\n    55→\\tfor _, opt := range opts {\\n    56→\\t\\topt(o)\\n    57→\\t}\\n    58→\\treturn o\\n    59→}\\n    60→\\n    61→// OrchestratorOption configures optional fields on the Orchestrator.\\n    62→type OrchestratorOption func(*Orchestrator)\\n    63→\\n    64→// WithHostRunner sets the HostRunner for host.cloche support.\\n    65→func WithHostRunner(hr *HostRunner) OrchestratorOption {\\n    66→\\treturn func(o *Orchestrator) {\\n    67→\\t\\to.hostRunner = hr\\n    68→\\t}\\n    69→}\\n    70→\\n    71→// WithParseHostWorkflow sets the parser function for host.cloche files.\\n    72→func WithParseHostWorkflow(fn ParseHostWorkflowFunc) OrchestratorOption {\\n    73→\\treturn func(o *Orchestrator) {\\n    74→\\t\\to.parseHostWorkflow = fn\\n    75→\\t}\\n    76→}\\n    77→\\n    78→// Register adds a project to the orchestrator.\\n    79→func (o *Orchestrator) Register(pc *ProjectConfig) {\\n    80→\\to.mu.Lock()\\n    81→\\tdefer o.mu.Unlock()\\n    82→\\tpc.Enabled = true\\n    83→\\to.projects[pc.Dir] = pc\\n    84→}\\n    85→\\n    86→// Status returns the enabled flag, in-flight count, and concurrency for a project.\\n    87→func (o *Orchestrator) Status(dir string) (enabled bool, inFlight int, concurrency int) {\\n    88→\\to.mu.Lock()\\n    89→\\tdefer o.mu.Unlock()\\n    90→\\tpc, ok := o.projects[dir]\\n    91→\\tif !ok {\\n    92→\\t\\treturn false, 0, 0\\n    93→\\t}\\n    94→\\treturn pc.Enabled, o.inFlight[dir], pc.Concurrency\\n    95→}\\n    96→\\n    97→// SetEnabled enables or disables orchestration for a project.\\n    98→func (o *Orchestrator) SetEnabled(dir string, enabled bool) {\\n    99→\\to.mu.Lock()\\n   100→\\tdefer o.mu.Unlock()\\n   101→\\tif pc, ok := o.projects[dir]; ok {\\n   102→\\t\\tpc.Enabled = enabled\\n   103→\\t}\\n   104→}\\n   105→\\n   106→// SetConcurrency overrides the concurrency limit for a project (runtime only).\\n   107→func (o *Orchestrator) SetConcurrency(dir string, concurrency int) {\\n   108→\\to.mu.Lock()\\n   109→\\tdefer o.mu.Unlock()\\n   110→\\tif pc, ok := o.projects[dir]; ok {\\n   111→\\t\\tpc.Concurrency = concurrency\\n   112→\\t}\\n   113→}\\n   114→\\n   115→// RegisterFromConfig registers a project using its config file.\\n   116→// Returns false if orchestration is not enabled for the project.\\n   117→func (o *Orchestrator) RegisterFromConfig(projectDir string, tracker ports.TaskTracker) bool {\\n   118→\\tcfg, err := config.Load(projectDir)\\n   119→\\tif err != nil || !cfg.Orchestration.Enabled {\\n   120→\\t\\treturn false\\n   121→\\t}\\n   122→\\tworkflow := cfg.Orchestration.Workflow\\n   123→\\tif workflow == \\\"\\\" {\\n   124→\\t\\tworkflow = \\\"develop\\\"\\n   125→\\t}\\n   126→\\tconcurrency := cfg.Orchestration.Concurrency\\n   127→\\tif concurrency < 1 {\\n   128→\\t\\tconcurrency = 1\\n   129→\\t}\\n   130→\\to.Register(&ProjectConfig{\\n   131→\\t\\tDir:         projectDir,\\n   132→\\t\\tWorkflow:    workflow,\\n   133→\\t\\tConcurrency: concurrency,\\n   134→\\t\\tTracker:     tracker,\\n   135→\\t\\tEnabled:     true,\\n   136→\\t})\\n   137→\\treturn true\\n   138→}\\n   139→\\n   140→// trackTask records a run-to-task mapping for later completion/failure.\\n   141→func (o *Orchestrator) trackTask(projectDir, runID, taskID string) {\\n   142→\\to.inFlightTasks[runID] = taskID\\n   143→\\tif o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir] == nil {\\n   144→\\t\\to.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir] = make(map[string]bool)\\n   145→\\t}\\n   146→\\to.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir][taskID] = true\\n   147→}\\n   148→\\n   149→// untrackTask removes a run-to-task mapping. Returns the task ID.\\n   150→func (o *Orchestrator) untrackTask(projectDir, runID string) string {\\n   151→\\ttaskID := o.inFlightTasks[runID]\\n   152→\\tdelete(o.inFlightTasks, runID)\\n   153→\\tif taskID != \\\"\\\" && o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir] != nil {\\n   154→\\t\\tdelete(o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir], taskID)\\n   155→\\t}\\n   156→\\treturn taskID\\n   157→}\\n   158→\\n   159→// isTaskInFlight checks if a task already has an active run.\\n   160→func (o *Orchestrator) isTaskInFlight(projectDir, taskID string) bool {\\n   161→\\tif set := o.inFlightTaskSet[projectDir]; set != nil {\\n   162→\\t\\treturn set[taskID]\\n   163→\\t}\\n   164→\\treturn false\\n   165→}\\n   166→\\n   167→// Run performs one orchestration cycle for a single project. It returns the\\n   168→// number of runs dispatched.\\n   169→func (o *Orchestrator) Run(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) (int, error) {\\n   170→\\to.mu.Lock()\\n   171→\\tpc, ok := o.projects[projectDir]\\n   172→\\tif !ok {\\n   173→\\t\\to.mu.Unlock()\\n   174→\\t\\treturn 0, fmt.Errorf(\\\"project %q not registered\\\", projectDir)\\n   175→\\t}\\n   176→\\tif !pc.Enabled {\\n   177→\\t\\to.mu.Unlock()\\n   178→\\t\\treturn 0, nil\\n   179→\\t}\\n   180→\\tcurrent := o.inFlight[projectDir]\\n   181→\\tavailable := pc.Concurrency - current\\n   182→\\to.mu.Unlock()\\n   183→\\n   184→\\tif available <= 0 {\\n   185→\\t\\treturn 0, nil\\n   186→\\t}\\n   187→\\n   188→\\ttasks, err := pc.Tracker.ListReady(ctx, projectDir)\\n   189→\\tif err != nil {\\n   190→\\t\\treturn 0, fmt.Errorf(\\\"listing ready tasks: %w\\\", err)\\n   191→\\t}\\n   192→\\n   193→\\t// Check if host.cloche exists for this project\\n   194→\\thostWorkflowPath := filepath.Join(projectDir, \\\".cloche\\\", \\\"host.cloche\\\")\\n   195→\\tuseHostWorkflow := o.hostRunner != nil && o.parseHostWorkflow != nil\\n   196→\\tif useHostWorkflow {\\n   197→\\t\\tif _, err := os.Stat(hostWorkflowPath); os.IsNotExist(err) {\\n   198→\\t\\t\\tuseHostWorkflow = false\\n   199→\\t\\t}\\n   200→\\t}\\n   201→\\n   202→\\tdispatched := 0\\n   203→\\tfor i := 0; i < len(tasks) && dispatched < available; i++ {\\n   204→\\t\\ttask := tasks[i]\\n   205→\\n   206→\\t\\t// Skip tasks that already have an in-flight run (dedup)\\n   207→\\t\\to.mu.Lock()\\n   208→\\t\\talreadyRunning := o.isTaskInFlight(projectDir, task.ID)\\n   209→\\t\\to.mu.Unlock()\\n   210→\\t\\tif alreadyRunning {\\n   211→\\t\\t\\tlog.Printf(\\\"orchestrator: skipping task %s (already in flight)\\\", task.ID)\\n   212→\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n   213→\\t\\t}\\n   214→\\n   215→\\t\\tif err := pc.Tracker.Claim(ctx, task.ID); err != nil {\\n   216→\\t\\t\\tlog.Printf(\\\"orchestrator: failed to claim task %s: %v\\\", task.ID, err)\\n   217→\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n   218→\\t\\t}\\n   219→\\n   220→\\t\\tif useHostWorkflow {\\n   221→\\t\\t\\t// Host workflow path\\n","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false,"persistedOutputPath":"/home/agent/.claude/projects/-workspace/3a4260cb-3063-4465-881d-24f718f4c0c9/tool-results/bczr8oh6z.txt","persistedOutputSize":4532638}}
