ep\",\"Edit\",\"Write\",\"Bash\",\"Agent\",\"TodoWrite\"],\"query\":\"select:Read,Glob,Grep,Edit,Write,Bash,Agent,TodoWrite\",\"total_deferred_tools\":18}}\n{\"type\":\"rate_limit_event\",\"rate_limit_info\":{\"status\":\"allowed\",\"resetsAt\":1772848800,\"rateLimitType\":\"five_hour\",\"overageStatus\":\"rejected\",\"overageDisabledReason\":\"org_level_disabled\",\"isUsingOverage\":false},\"uuid\":\"d2892c8e-df02-44b5-8418-b08a0497233d\",\"session_id\":\"599495eb-7ea9-4b8f-9d24-b0951537b876\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01DqhgVDa7b4b2V8HPCJGSxp\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"thinking\",\"thinking\":\"Let me start by reading the design document and understanding the existing codebase structure.\",\"signature\":\"\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10092,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":7472,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":10092},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"599495eb-7ea9-4b8f-9d24-b0951537b876\",\"uuid\":\"0d74964f-7086-4ca0-90f7-309a15fa8ddb\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01DqhgVDa7b4b2V8HPCJGSxp\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"text\",\"text\":\"Let me start by reading the design doc and key existing files.\"}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10092,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":7472,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":10092},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"599495eb-7ea9-4b8f-9d24-b0951537b876\",\"uuid\":\"9d90924a-db3f-4411-8db5-7fd24c97fae3\"}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01DqhgVDa7b4b2V8HPCJGSxp\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_015BdFwauPKAPkUc9CyzCayK\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10092,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":7472,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":10092},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"599495eb-7ea9-4b8f-9d24-b0951537b876\",\"uuid\":\"a5ac6560-22ed-4790-925f-f5dd120d7c00\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_015BdFwauPKAPkUc9CyzCayK\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→# Project Pages Design\\n     2→\\n     3→**Date:** 2026-03-06\\n     4→**Status:** Design\\n     5→\\n     6→## Problem\\n     7→\\n     8→The projects landing page shows only health dots and a \\\"View Runs\\\" link. There is no\\n     9→dedicated project page. Useful project-level information and controls are either missing\\n    10→or buried in other views.\\n    11→\\n    12→## Goal\\n    13→\\n    14→Add a dedicated `/projects/{name}` page with three panels:\\n    15→\\n    16→1. **Orchestrator control** — view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\\n    17→2. **Project info** — Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\\n    18→3. **Workflow view** — read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\\n    19→\\n    20→## Route\\n    21→\\n    22→```\\n    23→GET /projects/{name}\\n    24→```\\n    25→\\n    26→`{name}` is the project label (same string used in `/api/projects/{name}/trigger`).\\n    27→The handler resolves the label back to a project directory via `projectLabels()`.\\n    28→\\n    29→Project cards on the landing page link to `/projects/{name}` instead of\\n    30→`/runs?project=X`. The project page includes a compact recent-runs strip (last 10 dots)\\n    31→and a \\\"View all runs\\\" link to the filtered runs list.\\n    32→\\n    33→## Panel 1: Orchestrator Control\\n    34→\\n    35→### Display\\n    36→- Status line: `Enabled / Disabled`, in-flight run count, concurrency limit\\n    37→- Toggle button: **Enable** / **Disable** (controls the auto-poll loop for this project)\\n    38→- Concurrency override: number input + **Apply** button (runtime only, resets on daemon restart)\\n    39→\\n    40→### API additions\\n    41→\\n    42→```\\n    43→GET  /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\\n    44→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start\\n    45→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop\\n    46→POST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency   body: {\\\"concurrency\\\": N}\\n    47→```\\n    48→\\n    49→`GET` response:\\n    50→```json\\n    51→{\\n    52→  \\\"enabled\\\": true,\\n    53→  \\\"in_flight\\\": 1,\\n    54→  \\\"concurrency\\\": 2\\n    55→}\\n    56→```\\n    57→\\n    58→The orchestrator currently has no per-project enable/disable concept. We add an\\n    59→`enabled` flag to `ProjectConfig` (default true when registered). Start/stop toggle\\n    60→this flag. When disabled, `Run()` returns 0 without dispatching.\\n    61→\\n    62→Concurrency override updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in memory only.\\n    63→\\n    64→The Handler needs a reference to the `*orchestrator.Orchestrator` (or a minimal\\n    65→interface exposing `Status(dir)`, `SetEnabled(dir, bool)`, `SetConcurrency(dir, int)`,\\n    66→`InFlight(dir)`). Wire this in via a `HandlerOption`.\\n    67→\\n    68→## Panel 2: Project Info\\n    69→\\n    70→### Display\\n    71→- **Docker image**: read the `FROM` line(s) from `.cloche/Dockerfile`. Show the last\\n    72→  non-builder stage's base image (i.e. the stage that produces the final image).\\n    73→- **Project version**: integer, sourced from `.cloche/version` (see Project Versioning\\n    74→  design). Display as `v3`.\\n    75→- **Prompt file history**: for each file under `.cloche/prompts/`, show a timeline of\\n    76→  changes:\\n    77→  - List of git commits that touched the file (short SHA, date, message)\\n    78→  - Click a commit entry to expand and show a unified diff inline\\n    79→\\n    80→### API additions\\n    81→\\n    82→```\\n    83→GET /api/projects/{name}/info\\n    84→```\\n    85→\\n    86→Response:\\n    87→```json\\n    88→{\\n    89→  \\\"docker_image\\\": \\\"ubuntu:24.04\\\",\\n    90→  \\\"version\\\": 3,\\n    91→  \\\"prompt_files\\\": [\\n    92→    {\\n    93→      \\\"path\\\": \\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\",\\n    94→      \\\"history\\\": [\\n    95→        {\\\"sha\\\": \\\"abc1234\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-05\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"evolution: tighten scope\\\"},\\n    96→        {\\\"sha\\\": \\\"def5678\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-01\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"init\\\"}\\n    97→      ]\\n    98→    }\\n    99→  ]\\n   100→}\\n   101→```\\n   102→\\n   103→Implementation: run `git log --follow --oneline -- <file>` in the project directory\\n   104→via `exec.Command`. Diff for a specific commit loaded lazily on click via:\\n   105→\\n   106→```\\n   107→GET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=.cloche/prompts/implement.md&sha=abc1234\\n   108→```\\n   109→\\n   110→Returns plain text unified diff (`git show <sha> -- <file>`).\\n   111→\\n   112→## Panel 3: Workflow View\\n   113→\\n   114→### Display\\n   115→- Tabs if multiple `*.cloche` files exist in `.cloche/` (excluding `host.cloche`)\\n   116→- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\\n   117→  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent / script)\\n   118→  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\\n   119→  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\\n   120→- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\\n   121→  - Step name and type\\n   122→  - Results list\\n   123→  - `max_attempts` if set\\n   124→  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\\n   125→  - For script steps: the command string or contents of the referenced script file\\n   126→  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\\n   127→\\n   128→### DAG rendering\\n   129→Use a simple client-side layout: no heavy library. Steps are laid out left-to-right in\\n   130→topological order. SVG arrows connect boxes. For the initial implementation, a linear\\n   131→column layout (one step per row) is acceptable if the graph is a DAG with no parallel\\n   132→branches; upgrade to a proper layered layout when parallel branches are added.\\n   133→\\n   134→### API additions\\n   135→\\n   136→```\\n   137→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\\n   138→```\\n   139→\\n   140→Response:\\n   141→```json\\n   142→[\\n   143→  {\\n   144→    \\\"name\\\": \\\"develop\\\",\\n   145→    \\\"file\\\": \\\".cloche/develop.cloche\\\",\\n   146→    \\\"steps\\\": [\\n   147→      {\\n   148→        \\\"name\\\": \\\"implement\\\",\\n   149→        \\\"type\\\": \\\"agent\\\",\\n   150→        \\\"results\\\": [\\\"success\\\", \\\"fail\\\"],\\n   151→        \\\"config\\\": {\\\"prompt\\\": \\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\", \\\"max_attempts\\\": null}\\n   152→      },\\n   153→      ...\\n   154→    ],\\n   155→    \\\"wires\\\": [\\n   156→      {\\\"from\\\": \\\"implement\\\", \\\"result\\\": \\\"success\\\", \\\"to\\\": \\\"test\\\"},\\n   157→      ...\\n   158→    ],\\n   159→    \\\"entry_step\\\": \\\"implement\\\"\\n   160→  }\\n   161→]\\n   162→```\\n   163→\\n   164→```\\n   165→GET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\\n   166→```\\n   167→\\n   168→Returns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text).\\n   169→If the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly.\\n   170→\\n   171→## Template / file changes\\n   172→\\n   173→- New template: `templates/project_detail.html`\\n   174→- New page registered in `NewHandler`: `\\\"project_detail\\\"`\\n   175→- New routes registered in `NewHandler` mux\\n   176→- Handler struct gains an optional orchestrator interface field (via `HandlerOption`)\\n   177→\\n   178→## Not in scope\\n   179→\\n   180→- Editing workflow files from the UI\\n   181→- Evolution history of workflow structure (just current state)\\n   182→- Persisting concurrency overrides to disk\\n   183→\"}]},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"599495eb-7ea9-4b8f-9d24-b0951537b876\",\"uuid\":\"99028e4b-24db-4422-b9a2-fbec46e68680\",\"tool_use_result\":{\"type\":\"text\",\"file\":{\"filePath\":\"/workspace/docs/plans/2026-03-06-project-pages-design.md\",\"content\":\"# Project Pages Design\\n\\n**Date:** 2026-03-06\\n**Status:** Design\\n\\n## Problem\\n\\nThe projects landing page shows only health dots and a \\\"View Runs\\\" link. There is no\\ndedicated project page. Useful project-level information and controls are either missing\\nor buried in other views.\\n\\n## Goal\\n\\nAdd a dedicated `/projects/{name}` page with three panels:\\n\\n1. **Orchestrator control** — view status, enable/disable the auto-poll loop, override concurrency\\n2. **Project info** — Docker image, prompt file evolution history, project version\\n3. **Workflow view** — read-only DAG of steps/wires, drillable to prompt/script content\\n\\n## Route\\n\\n```\\nGET /projects/{name}\\n```\\n\\n`{name}` is the project label (same string used in `/api/projects/{name}/trigger`).\\nThe handler resolves the label back to a project directory via `projectLabels()`.\\n\\nProject cards on the landing page link to `/projects/{name}` instead of\\n`/runs?project=X`. The project page includes a compact recent-runs strip (last 10 dots)\\nand a \\\"View all runs\\\" link to the filtered runs list.\\n\\n## Panel 1: Orchestrator Control\\n\\n### Display\\n- Status line: `Enabled / Disabled`, in-flight run count, concurrency limit\\n- Toggle button: **Enable** / **Disable** (controls the auto-poll loop for this project)\\n- Concurrency override: number input + **Apply** button (runtime only, resets on daemon restart)\\n\\n### API additions\\n\\n```\\nGET  /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator\\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/start\\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/stop\\nPOST /api/projects/{name}/orchestrator/concurrency   body: {\\\"concurrency\\\": N}\\n```\\n\\n`GET` response:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"enabled\\\": true,\\n  \\\"in_flight\\\": 1,\\n  \\\"concurrency\\\": 2\\n}\\n```\\n\\nThe orchestrator currently has no per-project enable/disable concept. We add an\\n`enabled` flag to `ProjectConfig` (default true when registered). Start/stop toggle\\nthis flag. When disabled, `Run()` returns 0 without dispatching.\\n\\nConcurrency override updates `ProjectConfig.Concurrency` in memory only.\\n\\nThe Handler needs a reference to the `*orchestrator.Orchestrator` (or a minimal\\ninterface exposing `Status(dir)`, `SetEnabled(dir, bool)`, `SetConcurrency(dir, int)`,\\n`InFlight(dir)`). Wire this in via a `HandlerOption`.\\n\\n## Panel 2: Project Info\\n\\n### Display\\n- **Docker image**: read the `FROM` line(s) from `.cloche/Dockerfile`. Show the last\\n  non-builder stage's base image (i.e. the stage that produces the final image).\\n- **Project version**: integer, sourced from `.cloche/version` (see Project Versioning\\n  design). Display as `v3`.\\n- **Prompt file history**: for each file under `.cloche/prompts/`, show a timeline of\\n  changes:\\n  - List of git commits that touched the file (short SHA, date, message)\\n  - Click a commit entry to expand and show a unified diff inline\\n\\n### API additions\\n\\n```\\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info\\n```\\n\\nResponse:\\n```json\\n{\\n  \\\"docker_image\\\": \\\"ubuntu:24.04\\\",\\n  \\\"version\\\": 3,\\n  \\\"prompt_files\\\": [\\n    {\\n      \\\"path\\\": \\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\",\\n      \\\"history\\\": [\\n        {\\\"sha\\\": \\\"abc1234\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-05\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"evolution: tighten scope\\\"},\\n        {\\\"sha\\\": \\\"def5678\\\", \\\"date\\\": \\\"2026-03-01\\\", \\\"message\\\": \\\"init\\\"}\\n      ]\\n    }\\n  ]\\n}\\n```\\n\\nImplementation: run `git log --follow --oneline -- <file>` in the project directory\\nvia `exec.Command`. Diff for a specific commit loaded lazily on click via:\\n\\n```\\nGET /api/projects/{name}/info/prompt-diff?file=.cloche/prompts/implement.md&sha=abc1234\\n```\\n\\nReturns plain text unified diff (`git show <sha> -- <file>`).\\n\\n## Panel 3: Workflow View\\n\\n### Display\\n- Tabs if multiple `*.cloche` files exist in `.cloche/` (excluding `host.cloche`)\\n- Per workflow: a read-only DAG rendered client-side\\n  - Nodes = steps, rendered as boxes showing step name + type icon (agent / script)\\n  - Edges = wires, labeled with the result name (e.g. `success`, `fail`)\\n  - Terminal nodes `done` and `abort` rendered distinctly\\n- Clicking a step node opens a right-side **drawer panel** (CSS slide-in):\\n  - Step name and type\\n  - Results list\\n  - `max_attempts` if set\\n  - For agent steps: full content of the referenced prompt file (loaded on demand)\\n  - For script steps: the command string or contents of the referenced script file\\n  - Drawer closes via X button or Escape, returning focus to the DAG without page reload\\n\\n### DAG rendering\\nUse a simple client-side layout: no heavy library. Steps are laid out left-to-right in\\ntopological order. SVG arrows connect boxes. For the initial implementation, a linear\\ncolumn layout (one step per row) is acceptable if the graph is a DAG with no parallel\\nbranches; upgrade to a proper layered layout when parallel branches are added.\\n\\n### API additions\\n\\n```\\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows\\n```\\n\\nResponse:\\n```json\\n[\\n  {\\n    \\\"name\\\": \\\"develop\\\",\\n    \\\"file\\\": \\\".cloche/develop.cloche\\\",\\n    \\\"steps\\\": [\\n      {\\n        \\\"name\\\": \\\"implement\\\",\\n        \\\"type\\\": \\\"agent\\\",\\n        \\\"results\\\": [\\\"success\\\", \\\"fail\\\"],\\n        \\\"config\\\": {\\\"prompt\\\": \\\".cloche/prompts/implement.md\\\", \\\"max_attempts\\\": null}\\n      },\\n      ...\\n    ],\\n    \\\"wires\\\": [\\n      {\\\"from\\\": \\\"implement\\\", \\\"result\\\": \\\"success\\\", \\\"to\\\": \\\"test\\\"},\\n      ...\\n    ],\\n    \\\"entry_step\\\": \\\"implement\\\"\\n  }\\n]\\n```\\n\\n```\\nGET /api/projects/{name}/workflows/{workflow}/steps/{step}/content\\n```\\n\\nReturns the raw content of the prompt file or script for that step (plain text).\\nIf the value is an inline command string (not a file reference), return it directly.\\n\\n## Template / file changes\\n\\n- New template: `templates/project_detail.html`\\n- New page registered in `NewHandler`: `\\\"project_detail\\\"`\\n- New routes registered in `NewHandler` mux\\n- Handler struct gains an optional orchestrator interface field (via `HandlerOption`)\\n\\n## Not in scope\\n\\n- Editing workflow files from the UI\\n- Evolution history of workflow structure (just current state)\\n- Persisting concurrency overrides to disk\\n\",\"numLines\":183,\"startLine\":1,\"totalLines\":183}}}\n{\"type\":\"assistant\",\"message\":{\"model\":\"claude-opus-4-6\",\"id\":\"msg_01DqhgVDa7b4b2V8HPCJGSxp\",\"type\":\"message\",\"role\":\"assistant\",\"content\":[{\"type\":\"tool_use\",\"id\":\"toolu_01GKXWDfC22f4ePuZBU3w4WE\",\"name\":\"Read\",\"input\":{\"file_path\":\"/workspace/internal/adapters/web/handler.go\"},\"caller\":{\"type\":\"direct\"}}],\"stop_reason\":null,\"stop_sequence\":null,\"usage\":{\"input_tokens\":3,\"cache_creation_input_tokens\":10092,\"cache_read_input_tokens\":7472,\"cache_creation\":{\"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens\":0,\"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens\":10092},\"output_tokens\":9,\"service_tier\":\"standard\",\"inference_geo\":\"not_available\"},\"context_management\":null},\"parent_tool_use_id\":null,\"session_id\":\"599495eb-7ea9-4b8f-9d24-b0951537b876\",\"uuid\":\"13b74a63-8fa0-462d-ad78-729f09f8562f\"}\n{\"type\":\"user\",\"message\":{\"role\":\"user\",\"content\":[{\"tool_use_id\":\"toolu_01GKXWDfC22f4ePuZBU3w4WE\",\"type\":\"tool_result\",\"content\":\"     1→package web\\n     2→\\n     3→import (\\n     4→\\t\\\"bufio\\\"\\n     5→\\t\\\"context\\\"\\n     6→\\t\\\"embed\\\"\\n     7→\\t\\\"encoding/json\\\"\\n     8→\\t\\\"fmt\\\"\\n     9→\\t\\\"html/template\\\"\\n    10→\\t\\\"io/fs\\\"\\n    11→\\t\\\"net/http\\\"\\n    12→\\t\\\"os\\\"\\n    13→\\t\\\"path/filepath\\\"\\n    14→\\t\\\"regexp\\\"\\n    15→\\t\\\"sort\\\"\\n    16→\\t\\\"time\\\"\\n    17→\\n    18→\\t\\\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/domain\\\"\\n    19→\\t\\\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/logstream\\\"\\n    20→\\t\\\"github.com/cloche-dev/cloche/internal/ports\\\"\\n    21→)\\n    22→\\n    23→// HandlerOption configures optional Handler dependencies.\\n    24→type HandlerOption func(*Handler)\\n    25→\\n    26→// WithContainerLogger sets the container runtime for fetching live logs.\\n    27→func WithContainerLogger(c ContainerLogger) HandlerOption {\\n    28→\\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\\n    29→}\\n    30→\\n    31→// WithContainerManager sets a full container manager (logs, inspect, remove).\\n    32→func WithContainerManager(c ContainerManager) HandlerOption {\\n    33→\\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.container = c }\\n    34→}\\n    35→\\n    36→// WithLogBroadcaster sets the log broadcaster for SSE streaming.\\n    37→func WithLogBroadcaster(b *logstream.Broadcaster) HandlerOption {\\n    38→\\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logBroadcast = b }\\n    39→}\\n    40→\\n    41→// WithLogStore sets the log store for indexed log file lookups.\\n    42→func WithLogStore(ls ports.LogStore) HandlerOption {\\n    43→\\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.logStore = ls }\\n    44→}\\n    45→\\n    46→// WithOrchestrateFunc sets the function called when the orchestrator is triggered.\\n    47→func WithOrchestrateFunc(fn func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) (int, error)) HandlerOption {\\n    48→\\treturn func(h *Handler) { h.orchestrateFn = fn }\\n    49→}\\n    50→\\n    51→//go:embed templates/*.html static/*\\n    52→var content embed.FS\\n    53→\\n    54→// Handler serves the web dashboard.\\n    55→// ContainerLogger can retrieve logs from a container by ID.\\n    56→type ContainerLogger interface {\\n    57→\\tLogs(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (string, error)\\n    58→}\\n    59→\\n    60→// ContainerManager extends ContainerLogger with container lifecycle operations.\\n    61→type ContainerManager interface {\\n    62→\\tContainerLogger\\n    63→\\tRemove(ctx context.Context, containerID string) error\\n    64→\\tInspect(ctx context.Context, containerID string) (*ports.ContainerStatus, error)\\n    65→}\\n    66→\\n    67→type Handler struct {\\n    68→\\tstore         ports.RunStore\\n    69→\\tcaptures      ports.CaptureStore\\n    70→\\tlogStore      ports.LogStore\\n    71→\\tcontainer     ContainerLogger\\n    72→\\tlogBroadcast  *logstream.Broadcaster\\n    73→\\torchestrateFn func(ctx context.Context, projectDir string) (int, error)\\n    74→\\tpages         map[string]*template.Template\\n    75→\\tmux           *http.ServeMux\\n    76→}\\n    77→\\n    78→// NewHandler creates a web dashboard handler.\\n    79→func NewHandler(store ports.RunStore, captures ports.CaptureStore, opts ...HandlerOption) (*Handler, error) {\\n    80→\\tfuncMap := template.FuncMap{\\n    81→\\t\\t\\\"stateColor\\\":       stateColor,\\n    82→\\t\\t\\\"healthColor\\\":      healthColor,\\n    83→\\t\\t\\\"formatTime\\\":       formatTime,\\n    84→\\t\\t\\\"formatDuration\\\":   formatDuration,\\n    85→\\t\\t\\\"truncate\\\":         truncate,\\n    86→\\t\\t\\\"shortContainerID\\\": shortContainerID,\\n    87→\\t}\\n    88→\\n    89→\\tbase, err := template.New(\\\"\\\").Funcs(funcMap).ParseFS(content, \\\"templates/layout.html\\\")\\n    90→\\tif err != nil {\\n    91→\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"parse layout: %w\\\", err)\\n    92→\\t}\\n    93→\\n    94→\\tpages := map[string]*template.Template{}\\n    95→\\tfor _, page := range []string{\\\"projects\\\", \\\"runs\\\", \\\"run_detail\\\"} {\\n    96→\\t\\tclone, err := base.Clone()\\n    97→\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n    98→\\t\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"clone layout for %s: %w\\\", page, err)\\n    99→\\t\\t}\\n   100→\\t\\t_, err = clone.ParseFS(content, \\\"templates/\\\"+page+\\\".html\\\")\\n   101→\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   102→\\t\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"parse %s: %w\\\", page, err)\\n   103→\\t\\t}\\n   104→\\t\\tpages[page] = clone\\n   105→\\t}\\n   106→\\n   107→\\th := &Handler{\\n   108→\\t\\tstore:    store,\\n   109→\\t\\tcaptures: captures,\\n   110→\\t\\tpages:    pages,\\n   111→\\t\\tmux:      http.NewServeMux(),\\n   112→\\t}\\n   113→\\tfor _, opt := range opts {\\n   114→\\t\\topt(h)\\n   115→\\t}\\n   116→\\n   117→\\tstaticFS, err := fs.Sub(content, \\\"static\\\")\\n   118→\\tif err != nil {\\n   119→\\t\\treturn nil, fmt.Errorf(\\\"static sub-fs: %w\\\", err)\\n   120→\\t}\\n   121→\\n   122→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"GET /{$}\\\", h.handleProjectOverview)\\n   123→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"GET /runs\\\", h.handleRunsList)\\n   124→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"GET /runs/{id}\\\", h.handleRunDetail)\\n   125→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"GET /api/projects\\\", h.handleAPIProjects)\\n   126→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"GET /api/runs\\\", h.handleAPIRuns)\\n   127→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"GET /api/runs/{id}\\\", h.handleAPIRunDetail)\\n   128→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"GET /api/runs/{id}/steps/{step}/output\\\", h.handleAPIStepOutput)\\n   129→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"DELETE /api/runs/{id}/container\\\", h.handleAPIDeleteContainer)\\n   130→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"POST /api/projects/{name}/trigger\\\", h.handleAPITriggerOrchestrator)\\n   131→\\th.mux.HandleFunc(\\\"GET /api/runs/{id}/stream\\\", h.handleAPIStream)\\n   132→\\th.mux.Handle(\\\"GET /static/\\\", http.StripPrefix(\\\"/static/\\\", http.FileServerFS(staticFS)))\\n   133→\\n   134→\\treturn h, nil\\n   135→}\\n   136→\\n   137→func (h *Handler) ServeHTTP(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\\n   138→\\th.mux.ServeHTTP(w, r)\\n   139→}\\n   140→\\n   141→// --- HTML handlers ---\\n   142→\\n   143→// projectOverviewEntry holds data for a single project card on the landing page.\\n   144→type projectOverviewEntry struct {\\n   145→\\tDir        string\\n   146→\\tLabel      string\\n   147→\\tHealth     domain.HealthResult\\n   148→\\tRecentRuns []recentRunDot\\n   149→\\tActiveCount int\\n   150→}\\n   151→\\n   152→// recentRunDot is a minimal representation of a run for the mini history display.\\n   153→type recentRunDot struct {\\n   154→\\tID    string\\n   155→\\tState string\\n   156→}\\n   157→\\n   158→const healthWindowSize = 10\\n   159→\\n   160→func (h *Handler) handleProjectOverview(w http.ResponseWriter, r *http.Request) {\\n   161→\\tprojects, _ := h.store.ListProjects(r.Context())\\n   162→\\tlabels := projectLabels(projects)\\n   163→\\n   164→\\tvar entries []projectOverviewEntry\\n   165→\\tfor _, dir := range projects {\\n   166→\\t\\truns, err := h.store.ListRunsByProject(r.Context(), dir, time.Time{})\\n   167→\\t\\tif err != nil {\\n   168→\\t\\t\\tcontinue\\n   169→\\t\\t}\\n   170→\\n   171→\\t\\t// Convert []*domain.Run to []domain.Run for CalculateHealth.\\n   172→\\t\\trunValues := make([]domain.Run, len(runs))\\n   173→\\t\\tfor i, rr := range runs {\\n   174→\\t\\t\\trunValues[i] = *rr\\n   175→\\t\\t}\\n   176→\\n   177→\\t\\thealth := domain.CalculateHealth(runValues, healthWindowSize)\\n   178→\\n   179→\\t\\t// Take the last N runs for the mini history (most recent first).\\n   180→\\t\\tn := healthWindowSize\\n   181→\\t\\tif n > len(runs) {\\n   182→\\t\\t\\tn = len(runs)\\n   183→\\t\\t}\\n   184→\\t\\tdots := make([]recentRunDot, n)\\n   185→\\t\\tfor i := 0; i < n; i++ {\\n   186→\\t\\t\\tdots[i] = recentRunDot{\\n   187→\\t\\t\\t\\tID:    runs[i].ID,\\n   188→\\t\\t\\t\\tState: string(runs[i].State),\\n   189→\\t\\t\\t}\\n   190→\\t\\t}\\n   191→\\n   192→\\t\\tvar activeCount int\\n   193→\\t\\tfor _, rr :=","stderr":"","interrupted":false,"isImage":false,"noOutputExpected":false,"persistedOutputPath":"/home/agent/.claude/projects/-workspace/3a4260cb-3063-4465-881d-24f718f4c0c9/tool-results/boogso0ih.txt","persistedOutputSize":306948}}
